ruth davies blues night with special guest robben ford events at stanford ruth davies blues night with special guest robben ford facebook twitter email print add to calendar a longtime sjw faculty member bassist ruth davies has serious credentials in blues and jazz a short list of the artists she's toured or recorded with includes john lee hooker charles brown bonnie raitt van morrison maria muldar jimmy witherspoon clark terry and elvin bishop ruth's blues night at the stanford jazz festival has sold out nearly every year thanks to her uncanny ability to put together backup bands that would be headliners in most situations this year's band is one of her best ever featuring special guest robben ford on guitar ndugu chancler on drums danny caron on guitar john r burr and bennett paster on keyboards and charles mcneal on sax robben's been in the top five of everyone's best guitarist list since he hit it big with the original yellowjackets his reputation has only increased with his subsequent work with jimmy witherspoon joni mitchell george harrison and miles davis his most recent recordings have received rave reviews soul on 10 and renegade creation both of which find him laying down deep grooves with some of the jazz colleagues he's amassed over the course of his career if the blues were a swiss watch says all about jazz robben ford would be the watchmaker when sunday july 24 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where dinkelspiel auditorium 471 lagunita dr stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $38 general $24 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27977 more info last modified july 21 2011
